GINGER COOKIES
2 1/4 c all-purpose flour	1/2 tsp ground cloves
2 tsp baking soda		1 c packed brown sugar
1/4 tsp salt			3/4 c shortening or cooking oil
1 tsp ground ginger		1/4 c molasses
1 tsp cinnamon			1 egg

Stir together the flour, baking soda, salt, and spices.  Combine
remaining ingredients and beat well.  Add dry ingredients to beaten
mixture, blending thoroughly.  Form 1-inch balls.  Roll in granulated
sugar, if desired.  Place on ungreased cookie sheet.  Bake at 375 for
about 10 minutes.
